From 0c3442eb41d33b21b48e10715d15cd5d3764f4ab Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Prayers Loft Agent <agent@prayersloft.local>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 01:40:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] test(smoke): update stale selectors to match current Journal
 + Bible Assistant UX
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Root cause: two smoke-CI assertions still pointed at the pre-refactor UI.
Both fail against the current branch code — neither is a real regression.

Failing assertions
------------------
1. tests/tests/00-smoke-ci.spec.ts:59
   Old:  getByPlaceholder(/Ask any Bible question|devotional topic/i)
   Broke on commit ba792c7 (dynamic mode-aware placeholder). The old
   static text 'Ask any Bible question or enter a devotional topic…'
   no longer exists in the DOM.
2. tests/tests/00-smoke-ci.spec.ts:68
   Old:  getByText(/My Reflections/i)
   Broke on commits 8fff1ce + 6118c0e (rename + title-case). The page
   nav header, hero title, and empty-state title all now read
   'My Journal' — no occurrence of 'My Reflections' anywhere.

Fixes
-----
* Line 59: getByPlaceholder(/Enter a topic|Ask any Bible or theology/i)
    Tolerates either mode's placeholder so the smoke test doesn't
    need to know which one is default. Both are unique to the Bible
    Assistant screen so false positives are impossible.
* Line 68: getByText(/My Journal/i)
    Matches the nav header AND the empty-state title, so the test
    passes on a fresh CI database (empty state) OR a populated one.
* Test name also renamed for accuracy:
    'read-only My Reflections (journal) route renders'
      -> 'read-only My Journal route renders'
    Route path (/reflections-history) intentionally unchanged — that
    was the branch's stated policy (rename UI copy only, keep routes/
    component names).

No application code changed. No functional regression. This is a pure
test-selector refresh to catch up with the branch's own commits.
---
 tests/tests/00-smoke-ci.spec.ts | 17 ++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tests/tests/00-smoke-ci.spec.ts b/tests/tests/00-smoke-ci.spec.ts
index 02fed8b..c976c19 100644
--- a/tests/tests/00-smoke-ci.spec.ts
+++ b/tests/tests/00-smoke-ci.spec.ts
@@ -55,17 +55,24 @@ test.describe("@smoke CI gate", () => {
     await page.goto("/bible-assistant", { waitUntil: "domcontentloaded" });
     await page.getByTestId("bottom-tab-bar").waitFor({ state: "attached", timeout: 30_000 });
     await page.waitForTimeout(SPLASH_SETTLE_MS);
+    // After commit ba792c7 the placeholder became mode-aware. Default mode is
+    // "Devotional" → placeholder starts with "Enter a topic you'd like to
+    // study or pray about...". The alternate mode "Bible Questions" swaps in
+    // "Ask any Bible or theology question...". This regex tolerates either
+    // so the smoke test doesn't need to know which mode is default.
     await expect(
-      page.getByPlaceholder(/Ask any Bible question|devotional topic/i)
+      page.getByPlaceholder(/Enter a topic|Ask any Bible or theology/i)
     ).toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 });
   });
 
-  test("read-only My Reflections (journal) route renders", async ({ page }) => {
+  test("read-only My Journal route renders", async ({ page }) => {
     await page.goto("/reflections-history", { waitUntil: "domcontentloaded" });
-    // Page-level header is plain text "My Reflections". Empty state is
-    // also acceptable (test runs in a fresh CI database).
+    // Page-level nav header + hero both read "My Journal" after commits
+    // 8fff1ce (rename) and 6118c0e (title-case). Empty state is also
+    // acceptable (test runs in a fresh CI database) — that state also
+    // renders "My Journal" as the empty-card title.
     await expect(
-      page.getByText(/My Reflections/i).first()
+      page.getByText(/My Journal/i).first()
     ).toBeVisible({ timeout: 15_000 });
   });
 
